Forensic expert, Steve Kershaw, Senior Lecturer in Forensic Analytical Science at the University of Manchester told the
BBC: 'Even if we had lots more time and even if we had established that
it was a spade from the 60s or pre-dated the 60s, we would not have 
necessarily established if it was anything to do with Ian Brady.

'The only way we would have been able to
tell is if it had DNA on it and that is harder to tell with the handle 
gone (and) it being so corroded. Although some vegetation has survived (on it), there is very little chance of DNA having survived.'

Mr Bennett added: 'This "find" is of no help to us. A spade may well have been found again, but it does not tie in with any of the other information or evidence we have relating to Keith.

