'Their need for publicity and their 
desperation to get anyone to listen to them is evident from their 
pursuit of various individuals, usually as uninformed or as crass as themselves, on the internet.'

Claims emerged last month that Brady had
penned a letter - not to be opened until after his death - to Winnie 
that revealed details of Keith's burial spot on the moor.

Police launched an investigation and 
arrested Brady's mental health advocate Jackie Powell but the letter has
not been found and detectives believe it may have been a ruse by the 
killer.

